cs.SI, cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SD 

This paper deals with the analysis of the US patent citation network using network analysis techniques. It discusses the identification of historically significant patents and the development of metrics to detect recent trends in technical improvement. The paper's focus on network analysis and technology management suggests that it is most likely to belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). However, it also involves elements of Digital Libraries (cs.DL) in terms of analyzing patent citation data, Information Retrieval (cs.IR) in terms of identifying significant patents, Cybersecurity (cs.CY) in terms of detecting trends in technical improvement, and Software Development (cs.SD) in terms of developing metrics for technology management.
